questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application experiences a gradual increase in Heap usage, leading to eventual OutOfMemoryError (OOM) in the Old Generation. The application utilizes a custom thread pool via `ThreadPoolTaskExecutor` to process asynchronous tasks. A developer wrote the following filter to propagate security context using `ThreadLocal`:

java
@Component
public class SecurityContextFilter implements Filter {
    private static final ThreadLocal<UserContext> contextHolder = new ThreadLocal<>();

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {
        UserContext context = extractContext(request);
        contextHolder.set(context);
        chain.doFilter(request, response);
    }
}
